main event: A letter received in 1953 discussed the sighting of objects photographed during 1955-1956 in Shreveport, Louisiana.
interesting points: The letter indicates that there were objects believed to be photographed,The analysis suggested that the objects could be birds or possibly phantams,The sighting report was difficult to evaluate due to the long time interval and lack of supporting information,Technical analysis suggested that the objects may have been lights on water,The letters and enclosures provided did not seem to add anything new to the existing thoughts on such reports.
sighted object: objects believed to be birds or lights on water
